{"id":"decision-trace-dock-per-scope-store","type":"decision","fact":"The trace-dock Zustand store is per-scope: byScope: Record<eval|live, ScopeState> holds activeRunId/selectedSpanId/mode/costOverrideUsd. streamingState, height/heightPx, advanced_view, activeSessionId stay SHARED (one live SSE stream at a time). Each route owns its scope with an unconditional unmount cleanup; capsule visibility derives from useCurrentTraceScope() (/live* -> live, else eval); no 404 self-clear.","recommendation":"Read the scope slice via useCurrentTraceScope() in shell components (StripDockSlot/TraceDock/SpanInspector); route owners write a fixed scope. Do NOT reintroduce a global activeRunId or a 404 self-clear (both made the capsule follow navigation / flicker). Per-scope streamingState is deferred until eval+live stream simultaneously.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"human","reference":"trace-obs WS-2 operator-decided lean reshape","date":"2026-06-14"}],"tags":["frontend","state-management","zustand","trace-dock","observability"],"affectedFiles":["frontend/web/src/stores/trace-dock.ts","frontend/web/src/features/agent-runs/use-trace-scope.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
